Critically acclaimed, award-winning manga artist Takehiko Inoue doesn't pull any punches in this stunning portrayal of people struggling with serious life issues. Masterfully combining rich character development with beautifully detailed line art, Inoue, the creator of the mega-hit masterpieces Slam Dunk and Vagabond, lifts the manga medium to a completely new level of storytelling.

description:
From the author of not simple, House of Five Leaves, and Gente comes this powerful story. At the age of 21, Nicoletta travels to Rome to find her mother, Olga, who abandoned her long ago. Nicoletta finds her at Casetta dell'Orso, a charming little restaurant owned by Olga's husband. The staff of bespectacled gentlemen welcomes Nicoletta warmly, but Olga's reception is not so pleasant. Olga has never told her husband that she ever had children--and he must never know.

description:
Continuing the story of film pioneer Guy Ritchie's anti-hero, the Gamekeeper, soon to be a motion picture from Warner Bros. and producer Joel Silver (The Matrix)! Hoping to resume a quiet life as the gamekeeper of his slain friend, Jonah Morgan's estate, Brock is thrust back into battle when a team of hired-assassins kidnap Morgan's daughter, Krista, in a plot to steal the secrets of Cold Fusion. With the world's eyes on his home, an old enemy, the brutal, one-eyed Sadic, returns, leaving no rest for the weary gamekeeper. But when the connection between Brock's tragic past and a mysterious assassin is revealed, the Gamekeeper must do what he does best - kill - even if it means losing the last shred of his humanity!
